# Vibe Café — environment variables reference.
#
# THE ONLY VARIABLE YOU MUST SET IS GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT (for local dev).
# Everything else has a sensible default for a demo deploy.
#
# Three places these vars are used:
#   1) Local dev — copy to .env.local, npm run dev reads it
#   2) scripts/setup.sh + scripts/deploy.sh — shell env vars
#   3) Per-environment overrides — `.env.<project-id>` is auto-sourced by
#      scripts/deploy.sh whenever PROJECT matches. Use this if (for example)
#      your prod project should deploy to us-central1 and your dev to
#      europe-west4.
#
# Multi-environment workflow:
#   gcloud config configurations create dev
#   gcloud config configurations activate dev
#   gcloud auth login
#   gcloud config set project dev-project-id
#   ./scripts/setup.sh dev-project-id           # writes terraform/backends/dev-project-id.hcl
#   (optionally) create .env.dev-project-id with per-env overrides
#
#   # later, swap envs:
#   gcloud config configurations activate dev
#   ./scripts/deploy.sh                         # auto-discovers backend + .env

# ──────── Required (for local dev only) ────────

# Your GCP project. The app reads this for Firestore + GCS + Vertex AI.
GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=

# ──────── Optional: deployment knobs ────────

# Cloud Run region. Vertex AI Gemini image calls always go to the "global"
# endpoint regardless, so any Cloud Run region works.
# Default: europe-west4
# REGION=us-central1

# Cloud Run service name.
# Default: vibe-cafe
# SERVICE=vibe-cafe

# Artifact Registry repo (created by scripts/setup.sh if missing).
# Default: cloud-run-source-deploy
# AR_REPO=cloud-run-source-deploy

# GCS bucket for foam art + vibe images (created by terraform).
# Default: <SERVICE>-images-<GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT>
# VIBE_CAFE_BUCKET=

# Firestore collection for orders.
# Default: orders
# VIBE_CAFE_COLLECTION=orders

# Terraform state bucket name (created by scripts/setup.sh if missing).
# Default: <GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT>_tfstate
# TF_STATE_BUCKET=

# Skip the post-deploy revision prune. Default: 1 (prune runs).
# PRUNE=0

# Number of Cloud Run revisions to keep when pruning. Default: 3.
# KEEP=5
